The paper discusses the challenge of designing mechanisms that promote cooperation in Multiagent Systems, which falls under the category of Multiagent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also explores social dilemmas and network structures, which are topics related to Game Theory (cs.GT) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The proposed mechanism involves wealth redistribution, which is a topic related to Social Computing (cs.SOC) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MA, followed by cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.SOC, and cs.AI.
